AWS-HOSTED VIRTUAL CLASSROOM AND LEARNING PLATFORM
Project Report
Prepared By

Shreya Devarde

Domain

Cloud Computing and Web Application Development

Technologies Used

Python, Flask, AWS EC2, Amazon S3, Amazon RDS, Bootstrap, MySQL, Boto3

ABSTRACT

The AWS-Hosted Virtual Classroom and Learning Platform is a cloud-based educational solution designed to provide students and instructors with a centralized environment for online learning. The platform enables secure user registration and authentication, cloud-based content management, and seamless access to educational resources through an intuitive web interface.

The system leverages Amazon Web Services (AWS) infrastructure, including Amazon EC2 for application hosting, Amazon RDS for database management, and Amazon S3 for secure storage of educational materials. By utilizing cloud-native services, the platform offers scalability, reliability, and accessibility while demonstrating real-world cloud deployment practices.

The project aims to provide an efficient learning ecosystem that supports content sharing, course management, and resource accessibility for students and educators.

1. INTRODUCTION

Online education has transformed the way knowledge is delivered and consumed. Educational institutions increasingly require secure, scalable, and cloud-based solutions to facilitate learning beyond traditional classrooms.

The AWS-Hosted Virtual Classroom and Learning Platform addresses these requirements by providing a web-based system where students can access learning resources and instructors can manage educational content. The platform utilizes AWS cloud services to ensure high availability, scalability, and efficient content delivery.

This project demonstrates the practical implementation of cloud computing concepts by integrating AWS services with a Flask-based web application.

2. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Traditional classroom environments face several challenges, including limited accessibility, difficulty in distributing educational resources, and the lack of centralized content management systems.

The need for an online learning platform arises from the increasing demand for remote education, digital content accessibility, and scalable cloud infrastructure.

The primary challenge is to develop a secure and scalable system that allows users to register, authenticate, access learning materials, and manage educational content efficiently using cloud technologies.

3. OBJECTIVES

The primary objectives of the project are:

Develop a cloud-hosted virtual classroom platform.
Implement secure user authentication and session management.
Store and manage educational content using Amazon S3.
Maintain user information and course data using Amazon RDS.
Deploy the application on Amazon EC2.
Demonstrate practical integration of AWS cloud services.
Create a scalable foundation for future educational features.
4. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

The system follows a three-tier architecture consisting of presentation, application, and data layers.

Presentation Layer

The presentation layer consists of web pages developed using HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, and JavaScript.

Functions:

User Registration
User Login
Course Access
Content Viewing
Application Layer

The application layer is implemented using Flask and deployed on Amazon EC2.

Responsibilities:

User Authentication
Session Management
Business Logic Processing
File Upload Handling
Data Layer

The data layer consists of Amazon RDS and Amazon S3.

Amazon RDS stores:

User Accounts
Authentication Data
Course Information

Amazon S3 stores:

Course Materials
PDF Documents
Images
Videos
5. SYSTEM WORKFLOW

The system workflow begins when users access the platform through a web browser.

User Registration Process
User enters registration details.
Password is encrypted using hashing techniques.
User information is stored in Amazon RDS.
Registration confirmation is provided.
User Login Process
User enters login credentials.
Credentials are validated against database records.
Session is created upon successful authentication.
User is redirected to the content portal.
Content Upload Process
Instructor uploads educational material.
Flask validates the uploaded file.
File is stored in Amazon S3.
Content becomes available to users.
Content Access Process
Student logs into the platform.
Course materials are retrieved from Amazon S3.
Files are displayed and available for download.
6. AWS SERVICES UTILIZED
Amazon EC2

Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) is used to host the Flask web application. It provides the computing resources required to run the platform.

Amazon RDS

Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS) is used to manage user data and application information. It provides a managed database environment with backup and maintenance capabilities.

Amazon S3

Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3) is used to store educational content, including documents, images, and videos.

IAM

AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) provides secure access control and permissions management.

CloudWatch

Amazon CloudWatch is used for monitoring application performance and infrastructure metrics.

7. IMPLEMENTATION

The implementation phase involved the development and deployment of the application.

Frontend Development

The user interface was developed using:

HTML5
CSS3
Bootstrap 5
JavaScript
Backend Development

The server-side logic was implemented using:

Python
Flask Framework
Database Integration

The application connects to Amazon RDS MySQL for storing and retrieving user information.

Cloud Storage Integration

Amazon S3 is integrated using the Boto3 SDK to upload and retrieve educational resources.

Deployment

The application is deployed on Amazon EC2 and configured using Nginx and Gunicorn for production hosting.

